<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,581,714]" pageId="2" pageNumber="389">
The only species in the genus was described from 
<collectingCountry box="[735,795,581,606]" name="India" pageId="2" pageNumber="389">India</collectingCountry>
, West Bengal, but has subsequently been reported from 
<collectingCountry box="[151,251,617,642]" name="Thailand" pageId="2" pageNumber="389">Thailand</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[307,409,617,642]" name="Malaysia" pageId="2" pageNumber="389">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
(Ng 
<emphasis box="[469,526,617,641]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="389">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[534,592,618,642]" pageId="2" pageNumber="389" value="2014.0">2014</number>
) as well as the Society Islands in the Pacific Ocean (
<bibRefCitation author="Hoddle" box="[1193,1425,617,642]" pageId="2" pageNumber="389" refString="Hoddle, M. S., Hoddle, C. D. &amp; Mound, L. A. (2008 b) An inventory of Thysanoptera collected from French Polynesia. Pacific Science, 62, 509 - 515." type="journal article" year="2008" yearSuffix="b">
Hoddle 
<emphasis box="[1284,1342,617,641]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="389">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[1349,1409,617,642]" pageId="2" pageNumber="389" value="2008.0">2008</number>
b
</bibRefCitation>
). However, no information is available concerning the biology and host plant of this species. Within the 
<taxonomicName box="[1304,1436,653,677]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Scirtothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1304,1436,653,677]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="389">Scirtothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
genus-group it is unique in lacking ocellar setae pair I, the usual pair of pre-ocellar setae (Ng 
<emphasis box="[1197,1254,689,713]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="389">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[1260,1321,690,714]" pageId="2" pageNumber="389" value="2014.0">2014</number>
).
</paragraph>
